## Concept

When an agent first runs, its behavior establishes a baseline: how many tokens it uses,
how long sessions last, which tools it calls, in what sequences. Once enough sessions
have accumulated, drift detection watches for statistically significant deviations from
that baseline. Deviations are measured using Z-scores (standard deviations from the mean).

